{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"91831396-6120-4b73-8499-bbd4fc7b5d8b","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, you need to make these changes in your project file:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it — **Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default** in MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0. Removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` activates it automatically.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n\n- **Running tests:** `dotnet test` still works, but you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) since each test project becomes its own executable.\n- **CLI flags change:** e.g., `--filter` becomes `--filter` with slightly different syntax; use `--help` on the test executable to see available options.\n- **Extensions:** If you relied on VSTest adapters/extensions, check for Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents (most common ones like code coverage and TRX reporting have updated packages).\n- **CI pipelines:** Update any CI scripts that parse VSTest-specific output formats.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"427b1b7c-1591-4f96-b5e7-64568f073f2f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request in a specific repository.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":377},"id":"63908d4c-311f-4fa4-b7ff-81e000939c18","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:20:53.027Z","parentId":"e54b5ac2-828a-4616-99c7-0d72030d61d9"}
